50|$|Choir {{dress in}} the Catholic Church is worn by deacons, priests, regular prelates, bishops and {{cardinals}} when presiding at or celebrating a liturgy {{that is not}} the Mass, especially <b>the</b> Liturgy <b>of</b> <b>the</b> Hours.Before <b>the</b> <b>Second</b> <b>Vatican</b> Council <b>the</b> dress was more elaborate, and had dozens of varieties and colours. After <b>The</b> <b>Second</b> <b>Vatican</b> Council, it was reduced, however exceptions are sometimes granted for cathedral chapters.|$|R
